    "In the same year De Piles published his <em>Abreg\u00e9 de la vie des peintres, avec des reflexions sur leurs ouvrages, et un trait\u00e9 du peintre parfait,...</em> (The abridged lives of painters with reflections on their works and a treatise on the perfect painter,...).": [],
    "He partly wrote it during his confinement in the Netherlands.": [],
    "His last work, <em>Cours de peinture par principes</em> (Course on the principles of painting) appeared a year before he died.": [],
    "In his <em>Abreg\u00e9 de la vie des peintres</em> de Piles gives short historical accounts on selected painters, from Greek Antiquity up to the present, drawn from various sources, including the <em>Teutsche Academie</em> of <a href=\"/sandrartj\">Joachim von Sandrart</a>, the first part of which was published in 1675.": [],
    "De Piles focused primarily on those painters who in his view had contributed to the renewal of painting.": [],
    "The principal goal of his <em>Abreg\u00e9</em>, which interestingly begins with a treatise on the perfect painter, was to publish separate reflections on the oeuvre of the most famous painters, in addition to their life.": [],
    "Regarding Poussin, De Piles stated that he generally neglected the use of natural colors, and that he did not master the artifice of claire-obscure in painting.": [
